<br>
Consider this, the express reason for giving this item to him is to reduce his effectiveness in combat.  This could be considered an exploit due to the fact that the logic and AI of the game does not recognize that this NPC is a better fighter without equipping this weapon.  If this were a real person, they would not make that mistake.  It is poor logic in the game's programming that makes this reduction in fighting effectiveness possible.  Manipulating game conditions to reduce the fighting capabilities of a NPC due to poor logic in the NPCs design may well be considered an exploit by the administration/staff.<br>
<br>
I only made my original point because there are so few rigid guidelines on what is/is not a exploit that you might get in trouble for doing this.  This is a valid concern and I think it should be mentioned as a possible risk whenever a strategy like this is suggested.<br>
<br>
