/bow Mateo<br>
<br>
Thank you sir.  For the record, I despise the Verant EULA.  There are many provisions I feel to be unfair and since I had no chance to give feedback or negotiate it's points, and because I signed nothing, I don't feel bound by it.(This is in contrast to my lease contract. I went back and forth with my landlord negotiating each point, and we hammered out a deal.  I had no such input into the EULA provided by Verant, and as such I don't feel bound by it as a contract.  In fact the validity/enforcability of such EULAs has yet to be established in a court of law.)  <br>
<br>
But I do have respect for some portions of it.  One of those portions is that I will not try to use my knowledge of the design limitations, or flaws in the design as the case may be, to manipulate game conditions in my favor.  I have recognized many such opportunities, even in a short EQ career like mine, but have capitalized on none of them.  <br>
<br>
Is powerleveling an exploit?  I would in general say no, but the topic is debatable depending on the tactics used.  <br>
<br>
